          <img class="featurette-image img-responsive center-block" src="/assets/see_tho_2-750543817195d15c01b4b2e2f67117aa1ffb72652f79cd53e563e01824dad58e.jpg" alt="Generic placeholder image"style="
          width: 450px;
          border-radius: 5px;">




          <p style="text-align:center; margin-top:10px;">I have a confession to make: I primarily became Pengawas so I won’t get penalized if I was late to school. I’m sorry if I ever forced you to cut your nails, confiscated your handphone or chased after you for smoking cigarettes. Trust me, it did not give me joy to do all that while in super thick blazer and long skirt.</p>
          <img class="featurette-image img-responsive center-block" src="/assets/see_tho_pengawas-1485998b27cefe88feca5f1c5ef3015448290ae0696928d5ca1810d357b9ea8b.jpg" alt="Generic placeholder image"style="
          width: 450px;
          border-radius: 5px
          text-align:center;">

          <p style="text-align:center;; margin-top:10px;">
            What did give me joy was listening to my school friends, and helping them. When I was in Form 4, I decided to do Psychology because I liked helping people. After 4 years of studying Psychology, I still can’t read people’s minds, unfortunately. But Psychology did make me want to help people even more, and in bigger ways.</p>


            <img class="featurette-image img-responsive center-block" src="/assets/see_tho_now-b938a004b44576ec8569447bd22976135027aaddeafcf126abad0adec3d1de0d.jpg" alt="Generic placeholder image"style="
            width: 450px;
            border-radius: 5px
            text-align:center;">

            <p style="text-align:center;; margin-top:10px;">
              I now work with irregular migrants, such as refugees and undocumented migrants. I help them find home and rebuild their lives. I remember reading about them in our textbooks and debating whether these ‘pendatang-pendatang asing’ should be allowed in our country. I’m closer to the truth, but I still don’t have an answer to this debate. Helping people is not as simple as my Form 4 mind thought it would be. But I’m glad the simplicity of just helping my school friends has led me to helping people in need.</p>

